        <updateDate>2014-10-09T16:02:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Layoff Prevention Extension Act of 2014 - Amends the Middle Class Tax Relief and Job Creation Act of 2012 with respect to state short-time compensation programs that allow employers to reduce the workweek of their employees in lieu of layoffs.</p> <p>Extends federal financing of the programs for an additional year.</p>  <p>Extends through December 31, 2015, the deadline for a state to submit to the Secretary of Labor its application for a short-time compensation program grant.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
